article.headline: Jackson State 71, Montana 64
article.story: MISSOULA, Mont. (AP) -- Ishmael Joyce scored half of his 30 points from the free throw line Tuesday in Jackson State's 71-64 victory over Montana. The Tigers (2-3) held Montana's starting five to just 29 points as the Grizzlies (3-6) lost their fifth consecutive game. Joyce hit 6-of-11 field goals and 15-of-18 free throws while playing just 26 minutes. Leonard Taylor added 16 points and 15 rebounds as the Tigers outrebounded the Grizzlies 46-34. Montana rallied from a 30-25 halftime deficit to take a 49-45 lead on a 3-pointer by Roy Booker with 11:15 remaining. K.C. Cavette scored six of his 10 points during a 10-1 run that saw Jackson State take a 55-50 lead with 7:52 to play. The Grizzlies pulled within 61-60 on two free throws by Kamarr Davis with 3:00 left, but Joyce scored 10 of his points in the last 2:34 and went 8-for-8 from the free throw line in the final 2:04. Booker, a reserve, led the Grizzlies with 14 points and Victor Venters came off the bench to score 10. Montana's starting five was just 1-of-17 from the field in the first half and 8-of-35 for the game.
